title: Selena Gomez Declared Herself a Nasty Woman at Rihanna's Grammys After Party
text:
By Alyssa Bailey Feb 13, 2017 Selena Gomez, who did not make a formal endorsement during the 2016 election, showed what team she's on last night when she arrived at Rihanna's Grammys after-party at 1 Oak nightclub. Her jean jacket read "God bless nasty women ," and she wasn't the only one who wore it in her group: New picture of Selena tonight! pic.twitter.com/jQ1f3bjCO4 
â€” Selena Gomez News (@LifeWithSelG) February 13, 2017 Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Gomez was photographed arriving at this event with her new boyfriend The Weeknd, marking their first public event together. She appeared in several Instagram stories from inside too, though none with The Weeknd: [Video]: Selena via her Instagram Story. [Part 6] pic.twitter.com/rY2mm8u4wE
